# ovh_cloud_instance_autobackup

Retrieve information about an autobackup (Mistral crontrigger) for a Public Cloud instance.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/data-sources/cloud_instance_autobackup/example_1.tf"}}

## Schema

### Required

- `id` (String) Autobackup (crontrigger) ID
- `project_id` (String) Public Cloud project ID

### Read-Only

- `checksum` (String) Resource checksum for concurrency control
- `created_at` (String) Creation timestamp (RFC 3339)
- `cron` (String) Cron schedule pattern
- `current_state` (Attributes) Current state from the infrastructure (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--current_state))
- `distant` (Attributes) Cross-region backup configuration (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--distant))
- `image_name` (String) Backup image name prefix
- `instance_id` (String) Source instance ID
- `name` (String) Crontrigger name
- `region` (String) OpenStack region
- `resource_status` (String) Resource status (`READY`, `CREATING`, `DELETING`, `ERROR`)
- `rotation` (Number) Number of backup versions to keep
- `updated_at` (String) Last update timestamp (RFC 3339)

<a id="nestedatt--distant"></a>

### Nested Schema for `distant`

Read-Only:

- `image_name` (String) Image name for the cross-region backup copy
- `region` (String) Target region for cross-region backup

